        <h1>Jumpstart a Car Battery</h1>
        <img src="../../../assets/images/pictures/car_battery.jpg" alt="Car Battery" style="width:400px; margin:20px 0;">

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>If your car battery is dead, you can safely jumpstart it using jumper cables and another vehicle. Follow these steps carefully to avoid accidents.</p>

        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Jumper cables</li>
            <li>Another vehicle with a charged battery</li>
            <li>Protective gloves and eyewear</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Ensure both cars are turned off.</li>
            <li>Connect the **red (positive) cable** to the dead battery's positive terminal.</li>
            <li>Connect the other end of the **red cable** to the charged battery's positive terminal.</li>
            <li>Connect the **black (negative) cable** to the charged battery's negative terminal.</li>
            <li>Connect the other end of the **black cable** to an unpainted metal part of the car with the dead battery (not the negative terminal directly).</li>
            <li>Start the engine of the car with the charged battery.</li>
            <li>Start the car with the dead battery. Once it starts, remove the cables in **reverse order**.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Do not let the cable clamps touch each other.</li>
            <li>Wear gloves and avoid sparks near the battery.</li>
            <li>If the car doesnâ€™t start after a few tries, the battery may need replacement.</li>
        </ul>

